  <section cache:ref-path="03|04|04|.01">
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.01</num>
    <heading>Order of Payment for Unpaid Income Tax.</heading>
    <para>
      <num>A.</num>
      <text>Income tax payments received by the Comptroller shall be applied as follows:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>Payments accompanying returns shall be applied to the period covered by the return in the following manner:</text>
        <para>
          <num>(a)</num>
          <text>First to any penalty;</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <num>(b)</num>
          <text>Second to accrued interest; and</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <num>(c)</num>
          <text>Third to the unpaid tax.</text>
        </para>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>All other payments shall be applied to the earliest delinquent tax year in the following manner:</text>
        <para>
          <num>(a)</num>
          <text>First to any penalty;</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <num>(b)</num>
          <text>Second to accrued interest; and</text>
        </para>
        <para>
          <num>(c)</num>
          <text>Third to the unpaid tax.</text>
        </para>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>B.</num>
      <text>A refund of income tax due a taxpayer shall be applied first as provided for in <cite path="03|04|04|.01|A.|(2)">§A(2) of this regulation</cite>, and then in the following order of priority:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>To any debt collection intercept under <cite path="|03.04.05">COMAR 03.04.05</cite> or <cite path="|03.04.06">03.04.06</cite>; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>To the taxpayer of any remaining balance.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
  </section>
